content: SIX! THAT'S A WRAP! Back of a length around middle and off, Jos Buttler pulls this out of the park towards the deep mid-wicket fence and the ball has sailed over the fence for six. England beats West Indies by 7 wickets.
WIDE! Bumper, way too high. Wided.
Good length on off, Jos Buttler pushes this straight to the fielder.
That must've hurt Jos Buttler. Short-pitched, slower one. Jos Buttler swings early and gets beaten. Jos gets rocked in his abdomen.
Good length on middle and off, Jos Buttler tucks this to mid-wicket for no run.
Bumper, around off. Harry Brook looks to play the upper cut but misses out.
Good length around off, Harry Brook moves back and looks to loft the fielder at cover but gets beaten on the outside.
Back of a length on middle and off, Jos Buttler pulls this through mid-wicket for one.
Good length wide of off, Jos Buttler swings and misses.
SIX! SCOOPER TOO WELL FOR A SIX! Good length on off, Jos moves across and scoops this over the keeper for a biggie behind the stumps.
FOUR! A boundary to greet Alzarri Joseph back into the attack. Good length on middle and off, Joe Root moves to his leg and lofts this over mid off for a boundary.
Way too full on midle and off, Jos Buttler pushes this away for a single.
Quicker and flatter wide of off, Jos Buttler goes for a punch off the back foot but misses.
FOUR! Short of a length on middle and leg, Jos Buttler rocks back and poulls this flat and through mid-wicket for four more runs.
Way too full on off, Jos Buttler nudges this through mid-wicket for two.
Quicker one on the pads, Brook tucks this through mid-wicket for one.
Full and on off, Harry Brook drills this down to mid off for no run.
FOUR! Smashed away to the fence for four. Short-pitched on middle and leg, Jos Buttler pulls this flat and through the vacant backward square leg for four.
Jos has stepped on the accelerator. Good length wide of off, Jos Buttler shimmies down the track and swings at it. Misses out.
FOUR! Short-pitched, on middle and leg, Jos Buttler gets up on his toes and pulls this flat towards deep mid-wicket fence for four.
Good length on off, Jos Buttler rolls this to sweeper cover for a couple.

FOUR! A boundary behind the stumps as Jos gets lucky. Good length wide outside off, Jos Buttler goes for the a front foot drive but gets an inside edge and the ball just misses the off stumps and races to the fence fo four.
Short and wide of off, Harry Brook thupms this to sweeper cover for one.
Another single from Brook to end this over.
Pushed through on the pads, Jos Buttler rolls this long on for one.
Too full on off, Harry Brook pushes this to long off for one.
Too full on off, Harry Brook blocks this out.
Full on off, Harry Brook pushes this to mid on for no run.
Short of a length on off, Jos Buttler rocks back and smashes this to sweeper cover for one.
Short in length and on off. Brook defends it close to his body.
This is full and nipping in on middle and leg. Buttler flicks it to square leg for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Is there a twist in the tale? The man from the last match goes. Short in length and on middle and leg. Root stands tall to pull but gets a top edge to deep square leg where the fielder runs in and dives and takes it brilliantly. West Indies have an opening. Can they turn the tables?
Joe Root c S Joseph b A Joseph 44 (49b 1x4 0x6)
Too full and on middle and leg. Root turns it to square leg.
Outside off. Brook guides it to third man for a single.
A length ball outside off. Root looks to drive but splices it to third man for a single.
Too full and angling on leg. Root flicks it to square leg for a single.
One more run as Brook plays it down to long off.
Fuller delivery outside off. Root pushes it to long off for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Brook drills it to long on for one more.
SIX! Welcome boundary. Releases the pressure. Shorter and on off. Brook rocks back and pulls it over mid-wicket for a six.
Very full and shaping on middle. Root turns it to square leg.
Angles it onto the pads. Root clips it to fine leg where Shamar Joseph runs to his right, dives and gets a big hand on it. A single.
A good length delivery outside off. Root slashes his blade and misses.
A length ball outside off. Brook dabs it to third man for a single.
Length ball outside off. Brook punches it to cover.
Short in length and on off. Brook stays behind and defends it out.
Very full and angling on leg. Brook pushes it to mid on.
Wide! This is full and shaping down the leg side. Brook looks to flick but misses.
A single to end the over as Brook drills it to long on.
Flighted full and on off. Brook defends on the deck.
Too full and on middle. Brook plays it back to the bowler.
Slows it up and bowls it on middle. Brook blocks it out.
Very full and on middle. Root sweeps it to square leg for one more.
Short in length and on middle. Root pulls it through mid-wicket in the gap for a couple of runs.
Superb over from Joseph. Short in length and on middle. Brook defends it out.
Serves it full and on middle, angling in. Brook solidly blocks it out.
On a length and outside off. Root punches it to cover for a single.
This is full and on middle. Brook tucks it to square leg for one more.
A good length delivery outside off. Brook punches it to cover.
Leg bye! Bowls it full and from wide of the crease on middle and leg. Root misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. West Indies appeal but that was going down.
Tosses it up full and on middle. Brook nudges it to the leg side.
One more run by Root as he flicks this to deep square leg.
Floated on middle and leg. Brook paddles it to square leg and rotates the strike.
England working in singles. Short and outside off, this is slapped to deep cover for one run.
Fuller delivery outside off. Brook drives it past cover for a single.
Bowls it full and on middle. Root reverse sweeps it to point for a single.
A single to end the over as Root works it down to long off.
Flighted on middle. Brook eases it to long on for a single.
On middle and it turns back in. Root eases it down to long on for a run.
One more run as Brook plays it down to long on.
Flat and outside off. Root punches it past cover for a single.
This is full and on middle and leg. Root whacks it through mid-wicket where the fielder runs to his left and slides to save a couple.
Too full and on middle. Root turns it to square leg for one more.
An appeal for LBW but turned down. Very full and on middle. Root looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but probably pitching outside leg.
Full and outside off. Brook punches it through point for a single.
Slides it full and angling on middle. Brook flicks it to square leg.
Floated full and on middle. Brook blocks it out.
Flatter and on middle. Root paddles it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length on off, Joe Root plays this late and guides this to third man region for one.
Good length, drifting down the leg. Joe Root goes for the flick but misses out and wears it on his pads.
Short and wide of off, Harry Brook cuts this on the bounce to backward point.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Simply sensational from Brook. Pitched-up around middle and leg, Harry Brook gets right on top of the bounce and nails the on-drive to perfection for a boundary.
On a length around off, Joe Root drives this to sweeper cover for one.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root defends this out.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Tossed up on off, Ben Duckett looks to loft this over cover but fails to do so. Ben hits this straight to the fielder for a soft dismissal. Ben Duckett departs after scoring 58 (46).
Ben Duckett c E Lewis b R Chase 58 (46b 5x4 3x6)
Full and on off, Ben Duckett drills this ot mid on for no run.
Short of a length on off, Ben Duckett backs away and looks for the cut but gets it thumped off the inside towards silly point.
Quicker and fuller on off, Ben Duckett drills this back to the bowler.
Pushed through on off, Ben Duckett defends this out.
Tossed up on the pads, Joe Root flicks this to deep mid-wicket for one.
Good length on off, Ben Duckett defends this one out.
Back of a length on the pads, Joe Root tucks this through square leg for one.
Good length wide of off, Ben Duckett hammers this through cover for one.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Ben Duckett tucks this to the bowler left for no run.
Short and wide of off, Joe Root cuts this leaning back towards deep point for one.
No run.
Pushed through on the pads, Joe Root flicks this through square leg for one.
Quicker one on the pads, Ben Duckett drops this towards square leg for a quick single.
Too full on the pads, Joe Root drills this to long on for one.
Tossed up on the pads, Joe Root paddles this to short fine for no run.
Way too full on off, Joe Root drills this past a wide mid off and the long on fielder runs to his left towards long off and cuts it off. A couple taken.
Short of a length on off, Ben Duckett shimmies down and smashes this to deep cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Joe Root punches this back to the bowler.
Quicker one around off, Ben Duckett dabs this through cover and takes one.
FOUR! THREE ON A TROT! Length dragged back a bit, Ben Duckett gets down on a knee and sweeps this through the square leg region for yet another boundary.
FOUR! Pushed through on off, Ben Duckett swings at it, gets the outside edge and the ball races past short third to his right for four. Fifty for Ben Duckett.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Ben Duckett. Tossed up on middle and off, Ben Duckett sweeps this and the ball races through the carpet for a boundary to deep square leg fence.
Fuller on off, Joe Root nudges this to deep mid-wicket for one.
Pushed through on the pads, Joe Root goes deep inside his crease and rolls this to long on for one.
Full on off, Joe Root pushes this away for a couple.
In the air... safe. Tossed up on off, Ben Duckett lofts this on the bounce towards long off for one.
Quicker one around middle and leg, Ben Duckett blocks this out as well.
Full and wide of off, Ben Duckett blocks it out.
Arm-delivery, around middle and off, Ben Duckett defends this off the inside.
Floated on off, Joe Root defends this out.
FOUR! Reverse swept for a boundary. Tossed up, on off. Joe Root picks up the line early and goes for the reverse sweep. Nails it to perfection as the ball races wide to short third for four.
Fuller on the pads, Ben Duckett flicks this to deep square for one.
Quicker and flatter on off, Ben Duckett thumps this to short extra cover for no run.
Tossed up on middle and off, Joe Root drills this to long off for a single.
Fuller on off, Joe Root drives this to short extra cover for no run.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root tucks this to deep square for one.
Rock solid from Joe Root. Back of a length on off, Joe Root blocks this out.
Hits the hard length again, on middle and off. Ben Duckett gets an inside edge onto the pads for one.
SIX! UP, UP, UP AND OVER! Back of a length on the pads, Ben Duckett gets inside the line of it and flicks this all the way into the stands toward fine leg for six runs.
On a length around off, Ben Duckett pushes this back to the bowler for no run.
On a length around middle and off, Joe Root flicks this through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! This time, he finds the gap again and it has raced to the fence. Good length on the pads, Ben Duckett tickles this to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Fourth double of the over. Good length on the pads, Ben Duckett flicks this fine towards the left of deep square for two.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Ben Duckett flicks this through square leg for two.
Another couple as Ben Duckett finds the gap again.
Full and wide outside off, Ben Duckett thumps this into the surface and towards mid off for one.
On a length around off, Ben Duckett flicks this through mid-wicket and takes two more. Ben has been finding the gaps well.
Good length around the pads, Ben Duckett tucks this through mid-wicket and takes a single.
Spicy short-pitched delivery, body bound. Joe Root goes for the pull and gets it away high off his bat for one towards short fine leg.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Joe Root flicks this to deep mid-wicket for two again.
Good length on the pads, Joe Root rocks back and tucks this towards backward square. The fielder fluffs his lines and the batters take two.
Back of a length around off, Joe Root blocks this out.
AJ bends his back and follows Ben to his leg. Ben Duckett pulls this flat and into the surface towards deep square for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Jamie Smith has to walk back after Motie disturbs his stumps. Too full, around off, Jamie Smith looks to slog across the line but misses out and swings over. The ball sneaks under the bat and rattles the timber. Jamie Smith departs for 64 (28).
Jamie Smith b G Motie 64 (28b 10x4 3x6)

SIX! There is no stopping Jamie Smith in the Oval. Short of a length around middle and leg, Jamie Smith moves back and across and slogs this into the stands towards the deep mid-wicket region for six.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle and leg, Jamie Smith stirdes out in front and just helps this past the short fine leg fielder for a boundary.

SIX! FIFTY FOR SMITH! Tossed up around off, Jamie Smith shimmies down the track and smashes this up and over the long on fence for a biggie to bring up his half-century. Can he go on and score a ton? We shall see.
FOUR! A boundary through cover. Short and wide around off, Jamie Smith rocks back and smashes this through the cover region for a boundary.
Tossed up on the pads, Jamie Smith flicks this wide to short mid-wicket for no run. This was hit uppish but away from the fielder's reach.
Good length on middle and off, Jamie Smith tucks this through mid-wicket for a single.
LEG BYE! Too full wide outside off, Ben Duckett moves across and goes for the ramp but misses and gets hit on the pads. A single taken.
Good lenght on middle and off, Ben Duckett defends this out.

FOUR! A boundary now and Alzarri Joseph is thrown under the bus by Ben Duckett. Back of a length on leg, Ben Duckett once again goes for the pull and this time hits this closer to the fielder at deep square to his right but only for a boundary this time.
SIX! BACK-TO-BACK BIGGIES! Short-pitched again from Alzarri Joseph around leg, Ben Duckett pulls this one more time and clears the fence towards deep square leg region for six runs.
SIX! BEN GOES BIG NOW! Short-pitched, around leg. Ben Duckett gets inside the line of it and hooks this over the fence towards the fine leg fence for a huge six.
Length and on middle, Smith blocks it out.
Very full and on middle, Smith flicks it on the up to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
SIX! 50 up for England inside the fifth over. Shorter and on middle and leg, Smith gets tall and pulls it over square leg for six runs.
Good length ball on leg, Smith makes room to push it away but misses.
FOUR! Smith is playing a special innings. So many to put in the highlights column! Short in length and on middle, Smith pulls it to deep mid-wicket and it races to the fence.
FOUR! MORE RUNS! These are quality shots. Too full and on middle and leg. Smith drills it down the ground to mid on for a boundary.
Wide! Shorter and on middle and leg. Duckett looks to pull but misses. First, the umpire gave a wide and later reversed his decision.
This is full and on middle and off. Duckett blocks it out.
Short in length and on middle, Smith mistimes his pull to square leg for a single.
FOUR! YET AGAIN! Spills it full and angles it on the pads. Smith flicks it very fine and to the fine leg fence. Oh no, Shamar Joseph has overstepped. Not a good start at all by him. Free hit next.
Good shot for no run! Short in length and outside off. Smith hops and knocks it to cover.
FOUR! Smith is dealing in boundaries! Quality shot! Good length delivery outside off. Smith punches off the back foot, over point and it rolls to the fence.
1 run.
A good length and around off. Smith solidly defends it out.
Length ball shaping on middle, Smith clips it through mid-wicket in the gap for a couple of runs.
FOUR! That is a solid shot! Shot with a lot of confidence. Short of a length and on middle, Smith stands tall and punches on the up over mid on for a boundary.
This is full and outside off, swinging away. Duckett swings but gets a top edge to third man where the fielder overruns but does well to get a hand on it.
On a length and around off, angled away. Duckett drops it to cover.
Hard length delivery shaping on the off pole. Duckett blocks it out.
FOUR! England are off to a flyer! Good length delivery swinging it late on the pads. Smith waits and clips it past mid-wicket and it races to the fence. Not the best of starts from Shamar Joseph.
Touch fuller and around off, Duckett drops it to third man for a single to end the over.
Shapes across a length ball outside off. Duckett softly punches it to cover.
A good length ball, just outside off. Duckett leaves it alone.
FIVE WIDES! Shamar Joseph not able to control his line! Fuller delivery swinging down the leg side. Duckett misses his flick and it rolls past the keeper and to fine leg for four runs.
Leg bye! Too straight, full and on the pads. Smith fails to flick and it rolls on the leg side for a leg bye.
Leg bye! This is full and straight on the pads. Duckett misses his flick and it rolls on the leg side for a leg bye.
FOUR! Clips it away! Fine start for England. Length ball shaping on the pads.Smith helps it down to fine leg and it races to the fence.
FOUR! Off the edge! Jayden Seales swings back in a length ball on off, Smith looks to push but gets an inside edge past the stumps to fine leg for a boundary.
Wide! England are underway! Bowls it on a length and swinging down the leg side, by a long way and Smith misses his flick.
This is full and on middle and off. Smith punches it to cover.
Jayden Seales bowls it at 130 clicks. Length and on off. Smith looks to defend but inside edges it onto the pads.
Angles in a length ball on middle and leg. Smith nudges it to mid-wicket.
A good length ball, outside off, swings away. Smith shoulders arms to it.

OUT! BOWLED! A wicket of the final delivery! A good length delivery on leg, Motie makes room and tries to pull it low but misses and it crashes the leg pole. West Indies finish with 251/9.
Gudakesh Motie b M Potts 63 (54b 5x4 3x6)
Keeps it short and bowls it on middle, Motie looks to pull but misses it.
Serves it short and on middle, Joseph pulls but gets a top edge to fine leg where the fielder picks up on a bounce.
THREE RUNS! 250 up! Bowls a yorker angling on middle, Motie backs away and digs it out to point, past the fielder for three runs.
A single and Motie is on the strike! Length and outside off, Joseph drops it to point for one.
A DOT! Bangs it short and on middle, Joseph looks to pull but misses.
West Indies could have avoided the single so that Motie would have been on the strike for the final over. Length and on leg, Joseph makes room and slaps it to point for one.
Short of a length and outside off. Joseph slashes his blade but misses.

OUT! TAKEN! Alzarri Joseph goes after playing a fine, fine knock. Short in length and outside off, was the slower ball. Joseph looks to pull but top edges it to short third man where Matthew Potts tracks back and takes a really good catch.
Alzarri Joseph c M Potts b S Mahmood 41 (29b 5x4 2x6)
Goes wide of the crease with a fuller delivery. Joseph looks to slash it over but misses.
SIX! Joseph is playing a blinder here. Joseph opens up his body, sees a fuller delivery in the slot and tonks it over cow corner for a massive six.
Length ball, outside off, Motie slaps it to cover for a single.
FOUR! 11 runs off the over. Short of a length and outside off. Joseph swings across again but top edges it to third man for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! Bowls it very full and angling on leg, at 140 clicks. Joseph makes room and swings hard but misses it.
A single now as Motie punches it to deep point.
Bowls it into the surface on middle and leg. Motie steps across to pull but misses again. Good bowling.
Brydon Carse keeps it short and on middle and leg. Motie attempts to pull but misses it.
SIX! 250 still possible for West Indies! Short of a length and on middle, Motie clears his front leg and pulls it to mid-wicket for a biggie.
Full and outside off, Motie drives it through covers for a single.
Fifty for Motie! Certainly a match winning performance from Motie! He has kept West Indies into the game. Fuller delivery on off. Motie whips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Bowls it on the pads. Motie turns it straight to square leg.
Tossed up on leg. Joseph heaves it to deep mid-wicket where the fielder picks up on a bounce. A single.
Too full and on off. Motie flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and on middle, Joseph flicks it to square leg for a single.
Good over from Potts! backs his strength and bowls the hard length, outside off. Motie looks to ramp it over but misses.
Bowls the yorker on middle and leg. Motie plays it back to the bowler.
Drops it short and on middle and leg. Motie tries to pull as he gets very low but gets his eyes off and fails to connect.
FOUR! Matthew Potts pitches up a full ball on off, was the slower one and Motie has ample time to smash it past mid off. The fielder gets a hand on it but fails to stop it cleanly.
Potts bowls the off-cutter, length ball on off. Motie looks to cut but misses and it rolls just over the stumps.
Bowls a low full toss, just outside off. Joseph pushes it to cover for a single.
Tossed up outside off, turns in. Motie steps across and defends close to his pads.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it full and on off, Motie pushes it to cover.
Flat and outside off, this is cut to point.
FOUR! Motie moves to 44. Flighted full and down the leg side. Motie helps it as he sweeps it past square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Motie plays it back to the bowler.
Flat and outside off, tad short. Motie whacks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed up on middle, Joseph nudges it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Pulled away! Jacks drops it short and on middle, Joseph pulls it through square leg and it races to the fence.
Leg bye! Straighter delivery on the pads. Motie misses his clip and it rolls away for a leg bye.
Length and outside off, Joseph knocks it to cover for a single.

SIX! 200 up for the Windies! A good partnership is building up. Tossed up on middle, Joseph attempts the slog-sweep, looks to hit over mid-wicket but gets it straight down and over the fence for a six.
Flatter and around off, Motie hits it through covers for a single.
Very full and around off, Motie plays the defensive push to cover for a single.
Bowls it full and straight on middle, Motie blocks on the deck.
SIX! NAILS IT! Saqib Mahmood bowls a bumper on middle, Motie opens up his body and pulls above his head, gets right off the middle and down the ground for a six.
Hard length and on middle and off. Motie stays back to defend it out.
Digs it short and on middle and leg. Joseph pulls it to square leg for a single.
Short in length and on middle, Motie pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller delivery on middle, Motie bunts it to square leg for one more.
Tossed up on middle, Motie leans and blocks it out.
Shorter delivery, outside off. Motie cuts it hard and through point for a couple of runs.
Short and outside off, Joseph cuts it to cover for a single.
Flat and quicker on middle and leg. Joseph turns it to square leg.
FOUR! Greets Jacob Bethell with a boundary. Too full and shaping on middle and leg. Joseph swings and hits it over mid on for a boundary.
A single to end the over as Joseph nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and just outside off, Joseph rocks back and blocks it out.
FOUR! In the arc and gone! Fuller delivery in the slot on middle, Joseph thumps it down the ground for a boundary.
Outside off, this is guided to cover for a single.
Slightly short and on off, turns away with some extra bounce. Motie looks to push it away but misses.
Floats it full and on the pads. Motie helps it to short fine leg.
In-nipper, length and on middle, Joseph turns it to square leg.
Length ball on middle, Joseph blocks it back to the bowler.
Almost had him there! Brydon Carse sticks to his strength and keeps it short on leg. Motie tickles it fine and past fully stretched keeper to fine leg for a single.
Bangs it short and on middle, Motie sits under it.
FOUR! Another one! Not off the middle but still gets enough behind it. Serves it short and on middle, Motie pulls but hits off the splice over mid on for a boundary.
FOUR! Nice and fine! Lovely shot! Hard length delivery and around off. Motie strokes it past mid off for a boundary.
Wide! Shorter and going down the leg side. Motie looks to pull it but misses.
Tossed up on off. Joseph goes back and blocks it out.
Full and outside off, Joseph pushes it to cover.
Flighted outside off and comes with an angle. Joseph looks to drive but mistimes it to Rashid.
Floats it full and on middle, turning in. Joseph fails to defend and gets hit on the pads. That was turning down.
Flat and outside off, Motie strokes it past cover for a single.
Too full and on middle, Motie smashes it down the ground past mid off but the man from long off runs across and stops it. Two runs.
Wide! Too many wides from Rashid today! Full and well down the leg side. Motie leaves.
FOUR! IN THE GAP! Good length ball, outside ff. Joseph punches on the up and to the left of point for a boundary. A bit right and that was in the hands.
Serves it short with short leg in place. Joseph ducks under it.
Short in length and on middle, Joseph steps across to flick but misses and gets hit on the body.
Pitched up, outside off. Joseph drives it to cover.

OUT! TAKEN! Rutherford is in disbelief! He can't believe he didn't time that one! Was in the hitting region, short and on middle, Rutherford tries to pull but is late and cue ends his shot to mid-wicket where Harry Brook dives to his right and plucks it right above the ground. Excellent catch. Excellent change of bowling plan from Brook.
Sherfane Rutherford c H Brook b B Carse 70 (71b 9x4 2x6)
Short in length and on the hips. Motie bunts it to square leg for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the batter's end but misses. Rutherford was just in.
Tossed up on middle, Rutherford hangs back and turns it to mid-wicket.
Slower in the air, full on middle, Rutherford blocks.
Flat and way outside off. Motie slaps it to cover for a single.
Very full and on middle and leg, Motie nudges it to mid-wicket.
Slows it up, full and outside off. Motie shapes up for the scoop but misses it completely.
Floated full on off, was the googly. Rutherford drops it to point for a run.
Too full and on middle, Rutherford drives it to long off for a single.

Direct hit and Motie was a goner! Full and on off, Rutherford drops it to point. He calls for a single but eventually bails out leaving Motie halfway down. The throw comes in but the fielder misses his shy.
Floated and angling on the pads. Rutherford tickles it to short fine leg.
Leg bye! Full and shaping on the pads. Motie misses his flick and it rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
Angles it full and on the pads. Motie nudges it to short fine leg.
Pushes it way outside off, fuller. Rutherford drives it to point for a single.
Rutherford keeps the strike as this is punched to point for a single.
FOUR! Matthew Potts pitches it up, outside off. Rutherford leans and creams it through extra cover for a boundary.
Excellent stop! Length ball, outside off. Rutherford punches it to point where the fielder dives to his left and stops with both hands
Outside off, Motie punches it to point for a single.
Serves it short on the slower side on leg. Rutherford pulls it to fine leg for one.
Short of a length and around off, Rutherford knocks it to point.
FOUR! Motie might ask for more strikes after this delivery. Shorter and outside off, Gudakesh Motie cuts it last past short third for a boundary.
Fuller ball on off. Rutherford taps it to cover for a single. Rutherford in watchful mode against Rashid.
Tossed up on middle, Rutherford goes back and blocks it out.
Gives a bit more flight on middle, Rutherford knocks it to mid on.
Pushes it full and targets the stumps. Rutherford plays it back to Rashid.
Tossed up full on off. Rutherford blocks it out.
A dot to end the over as Motie ducks under this short delivery.
Wide! Spills it full and down the leg side. Motie misses his clip.
A slower length ball on off, Rutherford drops it to cover for one more.
Serves it on a length and around off. Rutherford defends it out.

SIX! Rutherford is keeping the intent going. This is a hit me ball. Slants it full and on the pads. Rutherford whacks it to deep square leg. Brydon Carse runs to his left and tries to take but palms it over the ropes. That should have been taken actually. Could have been a breakthrough moment.
At 131 clicks! On a length and outside off. Rutherford looks to cut but misses.
Pushes it full and on middle, Rutherford drills it to mid on.
Very full and angled across, outside off. Motie pushes it to cover. Successful over for England.
Flatter and outside off, Motie punches it to cover.
Wide! Tossed up on the pads. Motie misses his flick.
SIX! That's one way to face the hat trick delivery! Smash it out of the park. Slightly short and on off, spins in. Motie thumps it to long on for a six. Nothing delivery actually.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! West Indies are running out of batters. The leg spinner from Adil Rashid on a good length, around off, it spins away sharply. Chase has a feel for it off the back foot but edges it to first slip where Joe Root takes a simple catch. England right on top now.

OUT! GONE! Another one bites the dust! Very full and on middle and leg. Justin Greaves whips it low and flat to mid-wicket where Ben Duckett dives to his left and takes it. Important catch by Ben Duckett. Remember he dropped a couple of them in the last game.

Tossed up full and around off, Justin Greaves leans and blocks it out.

FOUR! Justin Greaves hits one now! Such a beautiful shot! Touch fuller and outside off. Justin Greaves firmly drives it past cover and it races to the fence.

Nicely floated, outside off. Justin Greaves pushes it to point.

100 up for the Windies! Angles in a full ball on middle, Justin Greaves hits it to mid on for a run.

Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Brandon King goes for the pull but gets it spilled off the toe end in front of mid-wicket. King is livid with himself as this was there to be hit away for some runs.
